                    <h2>Teaching Approach</h2>
                    <p>
                        We follow a simple, structured approach: clear chalk-and-board explanations, guided practice,
                        neat notebook work, reading periods in the library, and regular reinforcement through homework
                        and short quizzes. Group activities, charts, and map work help students express learning in their own words.
                    </p>
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h2>Assessment & Promotion</h2>
                    <p>
                        Assessment is continuous and age-appropriate. Across two terms, students are evaluated through
                        periodic tests, classwork, notebooks, projects (as applicable), and attendance. Parents receive timely
                        feedback to support study habits at home.
                    </p>
